<!-- SECURITY -->
<section id="security" class="security">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Security</div>
    <div class="section-title">Built to be unbypassed.</div>
    <p class="section-sub">Every security layer assumes the one below it has been compromised. We engineer for customers who have physical access, root tools, and technical knowledge.</p>
    <div class="security-grid">
      <div class="security-item">
        <div class="security-item-icon">🔑</div>
        <div class="security-item-title">Composite hardware binding</div>
        <div class="security-item-desc">IMEI + CPU silicon serial + SIM ICCID + baseband version fused into one HMAC fingerprint. Changing any single value triggers an immediate alert and lock.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="security-item">
        <div class="security-item-icon">🛡️</div>
        <div class="security-item-title">Play Integrity attestation</div>
        <div class="security-item-desc">Device attestation runs on every heartbeat. Rooted, emulated, or custom-ROM devices automatically fail and are hard-locked — no admin action required.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="security-item">
        <div class="security-item-icon">📜</div>
        <div class="security-item-title">Signed unlock commands</div>
        <div class="security-item-desc">FCM unlock payloads are RS256-signed. The app verifies the server's public key before applying any unlock. Replayed or forged commands are silently rejected.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="security-item">
        <div class="security-item-icon">💬</div>
        <div class="security-item-title">HMAC offline codes</div>
        <div class="security-item-desc">SMS unlock codes are device-specific, time-windowed, and ICCID-bound. A stolen code cannot be used on a different device or outside the 2-hour validity window.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="security-item">
        <div class="security-item-icon">🔬</div>
        <div class="security-item-title">Runtime threat detection</div>
        <div class="security-item-desc">Detects Frida, Xposed, Magisk, ADB, emulators, debuggers, and clock rollback attacks in real time. Any detection triggers immediate hard lock and a backend alert.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="security-item">
        <div class="security-item-icon">🧱</div>
        <div class="security-item-title">Hardware Keystore</div>
        <div class="security-item-desc">All tokens stored in Android Keystore with StrongBox/TEE hardware binding. Keys are physically unextractable — immune to EMMC dump and cold boot attacks.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

